.TH CMT 3 "2025-11-30" "1.0" "Maximum Tension C Library Extension"

.SH NAME
CMT \- modular and portable C library extension

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "CMT/CMT.H"
.br
.B #include "CMT/CMT.HPP" \- for C++

.IP "Optional Modular Include:"
Predefine
.B INCL__<MODULE>
macros before including `CMT.H` to selectively include specific modules:

.nf
#define INCL__FAR
#include "CMT/CMT.H" // Includes only the FAR module

#define INCL__INLINE
#define INCL__OBJECT
#include "CMT/CMT.H" // Includes INLINE and OBJECT modules only
.fi

.IP "Optional Sectional Include:"
Predefine
.B INCL__<SECTION>
macros to include entire sections:

.nf
#define INCL__KEYWORDS
#include "CMT/CMT.H" // Includes all KEYWORDS

#define INCL__ATTRIBUTES
#define INCL__KEYWORDS
#define INCL__RAX
#include "CMT/CMT.H" // Includes RAX, all KEYWORDS, and all ATTRIBUTES
.fi

.SH SECTIONS AND MODULES
Currently available section macros:

.TP
.B INCL__ASM
Includes all ASM-related features
.TP
.B INCL__ATTRIBUTES
Includes all attributes
.TP
.B INCL__CHECK_FEATURE
Includes feature-check macros
.TP
.B INCL__ENVIRONMENTS
Includes environment-specific definitions
.TP
.B INCL__FUNCTIONS
Includes standard library extensions
.TP
.B INCL__KEYWORDS
Includes all custom keywords

.SH DESCRIPTION
CMT provides essential tools and features missing from the standard C library, fully compatible with all compilers and platforms.  
If no
.B INCL__...
macro is defined, all modules and sections are automatically included by default.

.IP "Notes:"
- Defining an `INCL__<MODULE>` that belongs to a section already included via `INCL__<SECTION>` will not produce errors or warnings.
- Sections and modules can be combined freely to tailor the library to your project's needs.

